    "content_hash": "1705b33ac30fd173",
    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\nSnowflake is looking for an experienced, strategic self-starter to join our Executive Administration team within the Engineering Organization. In this role, you’ll partner closely with 2–3 Engineering Directors based in Europe (Berlin,Warsaw) to strategize, operationalize, and execute all administrative functions.\n\nYou’ll be an essential member of the leadership team, using your expertise in a fast-paced and growing environment to create structure out of chaos and help executives effectively scale the business. You’ll initiate, own, and implement systems and processes that increase efficiency for a growing org, keeping our global teams streamlined and aligned.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL DO\n\n - Master the Calendar: Effectively manage and maintain complex calendars for 2–3 Senior leaders, prioritizing a high volume of tasks across EMEA and US PST time zones.\n\n - Drive Engineering Cadence: Coordinate recurring engineering cycles, including staff meetings, technical reviews, updates, and calibrations.\n\n - Operationalize Efficiency: Build responsiveness into existing operations and define new regional strategies, such as optimizing onboarding and external event organization.\n\n - Global Collaboration: Partner closely with our US-based Admin team to ensure seamless cross-regional collaboration and alignment on global initiatives.\n\n - Event \u0026 Project Ownership: Execute high-visibility events, from week-long org-wide Hackathons to local team offsites (managing location, menu, and logistics). Lead small to large-scale projects including space management and headcount tracking.\n\n - Financial Stewardship: Manage team budgets, travel, and executive-level expenses. Process invoices, Purchase Orders, and conference-related logistics.\n\n - Strategic Communication: Facilitate communication between Berlin/Warsaw-based teams and global stakeholders. Own agendas for All Hands and offsites, and draft transparent internal comms (newsletters, meeting notes, action item tracking).\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL NEED\n\n - Experience: Bachelor’s degree and 4+ years of relevant work experience in direct executive support, program/project management.\n\n - Languages: Proficient English is required for global collaboration. Strong communication in German is essential for interacting with local vendors, Berlin office logistics, and regional stakeholders.\n\n - Agility: Proven ability to manage time efficiently and prioritize multiple stakeholders in an extremely fast-paced environment.\n\n - Problem-Solving: Experience identifying operational gaps and initiating the systems or programs needed to bridge them.\n\n - Precision: Extreme attention to detail, highly organized, and responsive.\n\n - Communication: Very strong interpersonal, verbal, and written communication skills; comfortable interacting with all levels of management, vendors, and customers.\n\n - Tech Savvy: High proficiency with modern collaboration tools and a quick learner of new internal systems, experience with AI agents will be a plus.\n\n - Culture: A passion for the Snowflake culture - someone who thrives on our values and \"puts customers first\" while \"acting with integrity.\"\n\n - Flexibility: Ability to adjust to rapidly emerging/changing priorities and to anticipate the requirements of your execs.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
